        <num>CC 1977</num>
        <heading>1977.  Obligation or performance by a third person</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1977.  Obligation or performance by a third person
The object of a contract may be that a third person will incur an obligation or render a performance.
The party who promised that obligation or performance is liable for damages if the third person does not bind himself or does not perform.</p>
        </content>
